# Third-Party Notices

This plugin depends on several skills from the upstream
[mattpocock/skills](https://github.com/mattpocock/skills) repository
under the terms of the MIT License.

## Installed Skills (not vendored)

No mattpocock skills are vendored in this repository. The setup script
`scripts/checks/install-mattpocock-skills.py` installs them verbatim
from the upstream repository into `~/.claude/skills/` under their
upstream names, recording provenance and content hashes in
`~/.claude/skills/skills-lock.json`:

| Skill | Upstream path |
|-------|---------------|
| `grilling` | `skills/productivity/grilling/` |
| `grill-me` | `skills/productivity/grill-me/` |
| `handoff` | `skills/productivity/handoff/` |

Seven previously vendored skills (`grill-me`, `tdd`,
`ubiquitous-language`, `improve-codebase-architecture`,
`obsidian-vault`, `write-a-skill`, `zoom-out` — the last briefly as
`mp-zoom-out`) were **removed** in favor of upstream-installed or
globally installed equivalents; vendoring alongside installed copies
produced duplicates, and `zoom-out` was deleted upstream. Load-bearing
content was inlined before removal:
`references/architecture-language.md` (from
`improve-codebase-architecture/LANGUAGE.md`) and the TDD/module rules
already inlined in `references/coding-standards.md` and
`references/plan-writing.md`. See `docs/skills-bundled.md`.

